sentences: Friedrich "Fritz" Hilpert (born 31 May 1956) is a member of the electropop group Kraftwerk.
Fritz Hilpert studied trumpet and percussion at the Musisches Max-Reger-Gymnasium, Germany, until 1976.
From 1978 he studied sound engineering at the Musikhochschule Rheinland and the FH Düsseldorf.
In 1986 he received his Diplom-Ingenieur qualification (the German equivalent of a Master of Science degree) in sound and image technology.
He worked as freelance sound engineer with several German acts as the new wave-band Din A Testbild before becoming associated with Kraftwerk in 1989.
In addition to studio work, he replaced Wolfgang Flür in concert when Kraftwerk resumed their touring activities in 1990, and engineered the album The Mix, released in 1991.
